================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

The UnitedAV source code (the C# package under unity/ and the native plugin
under native/) is licensed under Apache-2.0.

The built native plugin (libUnitedAV) DYNAMICALLY LINKS FFmpeg / libav, which is
licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL), version 2.1 or
later. UnitedAV links only LGPL-licensed FFmpeg components; it does not enable
--enable-gpl or --enable-nonfree.

FFmpeg / libav components used (LGPL-2.1+):
  - libavformat   (demux / mux)
  - libavcodec    (decode / encode)
  - libavutil     (shared utilities)
  - libswscale    (pixel-format / scale conversion)
  - libswresample (audio resampling)

Decoder/codec libraries reached through FFmpeg may carry their own permissive
licenses, e.g. dav1d (BSD, AV1), libvpx (BSD, VP8/VP9), and libopus (BSD, Opus).

LGPL obligations for binary redistribution
------------------------------------------
When redistributing a built plugin that links FFmpeg, you must honor the LGPL:

  - Ship FFmpeg as separate, replaceable shared libraries (dynamic linking), so
    a recipient can relink the plugin against a modified FFmpeg.
  - Provide the corresponding FFmpeg source (or a written offer / link) for the
    exact FFmpeg build shipped, along with the configure flags used.
  - Include FFmpeg's license texts and attribution notices.

See docs/licensing.md for details.
